<subSubSection pageId="116" pageNumber="394" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="116.[2059,2656,2940,3362]" pageId="116" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="J. A. Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[2063,2325,3058,3087]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="116" pageNumber="394" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nasutus">Peromyscus nasutus</taxonomicName>
is in the true: species group. Initially described as a species, it was later placed as a subspecies of P. dif ficilis. Chromosome, allozyme, and DNA studies have confirmed that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="J. A. Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[2509,2656,3211,3244]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="116" pageNumber="394" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nasutus">P. nasutus</taxonomicName>
should be recognized as a species separate from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="J. A. Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[2226,2374,3290,3323]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="116" pageNumber="394" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="difficilis">P. difficilis</taxonomicName>
. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="117" lastPageNumber="395" pageId="116" pageNumber="394" type="synonymic_list">
